.START 

South Korean trade with communist countries for the first half of the year rose 38% to $2.08 billion, compared with the year-ago period, the Trade and Industry Ministry said. 

Officials said China was South Korea's biggest communist trading partner for the first six months of this year when their two-way trade was listed at $1.62 billion.
Trade between South Korea and the Soviet Union was listed at $270 million. 

The six-month trade total accounted for 4.1% of South Korea's global trade of $50.6 billion for the same period. 

Between January and June, South Korean exports to communist countries totaled $985 million, up 29% from a year ago.
South Korean imports from these countries jumped 48% to $1.1 billion. 

